reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just sounds funny
reviews.reviewText: First impressions of this unit are pretty decent. Vetroo has never failed to impress me, so I had high hopes for this PSU. The presentation is pretty good all things considered. The power supply itself comes in a black pouch and the cables are in their own box. The modular cables are all tied with Velcro straps, so the extra cable management is greatly appreciated. Though, Vetroo does bundle in some bigger Velcro straps.Installation is about what you'd expect of a computer power supply. You install the cables you want, screw it into the case, I won't bore you with the age old process. Though, it's worth pointing out that this PSU has built-in PCI-E 5.0 cables which is very nice to see, especially at this price point. I'm currently not at max capacity of this unit with the system I'm using this with, but this is great as I have plenty of headroom for upgrading to beefier components. At any rate, it does a splendid job of powering my system.When it comes to sound levels, this is honestly where this unit falls short. I do not have the knowhow nor resources to determine the quality of what's inside this power supply, but whatever they're using, there's some coil whine. This isn't terribly uncommon, but in all my years of computer building, this is the first time I've had this issue with a power supply. The second the unit is fired up, there's a very faint amount of coil whine. The fan is also a little annoying, even at idle. I may need to experiment some more, but ECO mode doesn't seem to impact noise levels. This may be something that will go away with age, but something to keep in mind when getting this. Noise is tolerable however as I have hard drives and 5 case fans, though your mileage may vary.Overall, for the price, with the decent feature set and seemingly decent build-quality, if Vetroo honors their 10-year warranty, you honestly can't go wrong with this power supply.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this PSU!
reviews.reviewText: It is a great little unit. 1000w with the cables being a little difficult, but the white with the black ends really make it look good. Plenty of power to run everything even if you have a GPU that is an energy hog. Quiet matches my case, and at a great price, fast shipping and 10-year warranty! What more could you ask for? Time will tell, the longer it lasts the better the deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Bang for Buck!
reviews.reviewText: Scored this baby when my EVGA 1000w PSU started coil whining and had some crashing during heavy gaming sessions. I slapped this bad boy in and no more crashes and steady consistent power delivery to my pc components. Works perfectly fine in an AMD 5800X3D, 7900XTX combo build. I am unfamiliar with the Cybanetics testing, but it was displayed on the image for the front cover on the description, yet it wasn't anywhere on the box or in the manual that came with it so Idk if that's accurate.I have built many PC's for myself and my family over the years and I wouldn't say I'm pro, but slightly above amateurish and have no problems with cable management using this psu. The wires for the 24pin to MOBO is robust yurr gayy so getting it to fold and cable tie it was surprising as it was very bulky, but still able to hide under the covering inside the chassis.Overall quite happy with the purchase, and as long as Vetroo honors the pirate code of honoring the warranty if it fails then its a steal of a deal for 120 buckeronies!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Took a chance and it was worth it
reviews.reviewText: Was looking far a 1000w supply for a new all-white build, stumbled upon this guy. The price was stellar, so I thought OK it has to be kinda crappy. Read reviews, and people were saying it has bad coil whine, but not everyone. So I figured if it's really bad, I can just return it. I've had it for about a month and a half now, and it's been flawless. No noise whatsoever. Handles my 7900xtx just fine. I like that it comes with all white cabling also, really helps cut down on buying extenders to complete the aesthetic. Even comes with white velcro straps. Also pretty great that it comes with ATX3.0 and PCIe5.0 hookups, so it's also future-resistant. Overall I'm super happy, I don't know if this is some up and coming brand or what, but I have confidence in them now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Warranty not honored. Great until it dies. Vetroo customer service won't help you.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this 8 months ago. My estimated power draw for my build is 475w, well below the limit of this PSU. It worked wonderfully, came with great cables, and felt very well-made. Then, after 8 months, I was 5 minutes into gaming and it just died.If you look at the ad (and title) for this PSU, it says "10 year warranty." So, I reached out to the company as instructed to utilize the warranty. They acknowledged this product does indeed have a 10 year warranty. When asking them how to utilize the warranty, Vetroo stopped responding. So, there is a warranty, but good luck trying to use it as they will not respond to you.I am absolutely disappointed with this purchase as the warranty was one of the reasons I took a gamble on this brand. So, if you are okay with knowing they will not help you utilize the warranty and that you are out of luck if it dies, then I hope it works out well for you. As of now, I will never buy from this company again because they do not standby by their own products nor will they help you outside of Amazon's 30 day return window.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best bang for the buck!
reviews.reviewText: Got this about a week ago. Very good price for this type of PSU. Install was easy, cables included were good quality, and no issues reaching mobo, cpu, etc. Have had no isssues at all. I reached out to Vetroo about the warranty and they responded pretty quickly.Minor issue: It isnt a super quiet fan, but quiet enough for most people. If you want a super quiet fan I would look elsewhere.UPDATE: I Just got a 7900xt and going to put this through some testing at high loads. Will update when done.Did some testing using Heaven benchmark. It basically puts your gpu/psu through an incredible amount of strain. It pushes your gpu to the limit (and goes way beyond everyday use), and psu has to supply alot more power. Anyway, let the test run for 35 minutes and both GPU and PSU passed with flying colors

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was a bit hesitant to get the Vetroo 1000W PSU as it had a good review on the Hardware Busters website though it had been removed as a few people reported a noisy fan. Also as it was not a tier 1 vendor like Seasonic, Superflower and the majors like Corsair, EVGA, NZXT and Asus etc. it was a bit of a worry but the pricing for an ATX 3.0 and PCIe 5.0 ready PSU was exceptional, especially for a 1000w unit.Overall this is a very well made PSU, it is compact with all the cables included with the added bonus of the cables being colour coded, so in my case, all the cables are white to go with the white PSU. Easy of installation was great and everything went together with no issues and all the cables are modular so you only use what you have to. The dedicated 16 pin GPU cable is perfect and fit very well to the 4090 so again no issues.I am running a fairly powerful PC with a 13700K overclocked and a RTX 4090 but this PSU handled this with no issues even when stress testing! Sound though it can get a bit loud at full tilt was not an issue and with the eco mode it is wisper quiet and with normal use like gaming, you will not hear this PSU...I will provide an update in 6 months or before should anything go wrong but for the moment, this is a great value PSU.

reviews.reviewTitle: 今のところ何の問題も不満もない
reviews.reviewText: Ryzen 9 7950x3dとRTX4090の組み合わせで使用しています。購入にあたっては聞いたこともないメーカーの商品であることが不安でしたが、RTX4090と組み合わせても現状何の問題もありません。まだ1か月少々の使用でしかありませんが何の不満もなく、購入時の価格が16499円とATX3.0 1000W電源としては格安だったこともあり、満足度は非常に高いです。また、このクラスの電源としては今現在、非常に貴重なホワイト色を手に入れることができたのも良かったです。あとは10年保証を信じて耐久性に期待したいと思います。

I took a bit of a risk here because this brand isn't well known for PSUs. But Cybernetics and Cultists rated it highly, so I tried it out. No issues so far.No issues with coil whine like some people experienced.

reviews.reviewTitle: 品質のいい電源ユニットだと思います
reviews.reviewText: ATX3.0 1000wフルモジュラーにしてはコスパいいと思います。見た目もスタイリッシュな感じあって、何より16PinのRTX40シリーズが1本で接続できるのがすごく感動しました。本体にエコモードが付いてますけど、なくても割と静かでした。付属品は、本体と巾着タイプのケース、ケーブル各種、電源ケーブル(日本でも使える規格)、マジックテープ、取説。日本のレビューなくて、あんまり聞いたことないメーカーさんで心配だったけど、今のところ問題なく使えてます。また何かあれば追記します。
